Text.Value: Now come - we had best get to saving it, lest Rion turn her ire on us both.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - From "I met your family. Rion..."

Text.Value: I'd like to hear more about those old days.
Hah! A kind way of saying: 'Ye gods, I hope her dusty bones don't break at the first blow.'
Do you know, maybe my hearing is not what it was. Would you like to repeat that?

EditorData.NodeContext: Playing into the joke of her being old - but a friendly note of threat at the end

Text.Value: No. Quite the opposite, in fact. I hoped to greet my family when all the fighting was done.
Then ask.
Admit it - you were just afraid of Rion.
Of course I was! You met her, did you not? The girl had opinions before she had teeth.
You think me lonely? In truth, I prefer travel in a small pack such as this.

EditorData.NodeContext: Arched eyebrow, vaguely amused at why we're checking on her

Text.Value: Just try to keep up, old one.
Come on, then. Likely you have some pointed questions, but you shall have to get in line behind my dear, dear daughter.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Back to main questions "Speak."

Text.Value: You're right. That is extremely foolish.
I was wrong to think I could keep my children from this fight. They're Baldurian born and bred - the only damned reason I root myself in this place.
Unburdened by numbers, we're free to act - rather than react. A little like the old days.
Well, if fool I be, then at least I'm in good company.
I understand. I think I would have done the same.
And if this fight were to go against us, well... they had already done their mourning. Why visit it on them twice?
With allies every bit as peculiar - give or take a few tadpoles.
Your experience will be an asset.
Would you? In time, then. Perhaps once you've found a rocking chair for me to doze off in.

EditorData.NodeContext: Amused that we're asking about stories of the good old days, but more focused on the task at hand. Putting us off, but not harshly.

Text.Value: I wanted to ask about something else.
Fear not for me. I will try my very best to keep up.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dryly amused. Your abilities are being questioned due to your age - you look forward to surprising the questioner.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - From "How are you faring without your Harpers"

Text.Value: ...Ah. You've wandered far in my absence. And now you come to march me to the gallows, is it?
I have given you much reason to think that Harpers hoard secrets like precious stones. But I promise you, this was not some intrigue.
It also happens to be their home - and so it is mine. Ugh... that might be the first time I have said that out loud.
Do you have so little faith in our chances of victory?

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - From "Why didn't you tell me about your family"

Text.Value: This city is a cesspit. An open sewer of the soul, that taints us with its filth, and churns us out when all that is good has been stripped away.
Careful, now. Only I get to say it. And my daughter, apparently.
Just... plain and simple foolishness. As if by keeping clear of my family, I might keep them clear of the cult in turn.

Synopsis: Jaheira's default dialogue. Topics range from her past life to her current goals as they develop. Unless otherwise stated, her tone is confident and to the point. She's a seasoned adventurer with a sardonic sense of humour - and a little less cynical than she might present herself to be.
